The paper deals with approximation algorithms for a graph problem involving connectivity and domination, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category, as the paper focuses on designing algorithms for a specific problem. "cs.NA" (Numerical Analysis) is also likely, as the paper involves analyzing the approximation ratios of the algorithms. "cs.CG" (Computational Geometry) is another possibility, as the paper deals with unit disc graphs. "cs.DM" (Discrete Mathematics) and "cs.GT" (Computer Science and Game Theory) are also possible categories, as the problem involves graph theory and optimization.
